Comments: The Rhodospirillaceae are a fairly heterogeneous collection of purple bacteria. The genome sequence of Roseospira marina DSM15113 is one of the more divergent members of the non-sulfur purple photosynthetic bacterial family.
Genome sequencing of Purple Non-Sulfur Bacteria to expand its genomic potential for discovery
Genome sequencing as part of The One Thousand Microbial Genomes Phase 4 (KMG IV) project
Roseospira navarrensis is a purple nonsulfur bacteria, belonging to the alpha-Proteobacteria. We sequenced the genome of R. navarrensis strain DSM15114, type strain.
